    "insights_summary": "The plant HOPS tethering complex is evolutionarily conserved with other eukaryotes and is involved in vacuole traffic via a RAB7-mediated pathway. HOPS shares four subunits with CORVET, a similar conserved complex that mediates tethering of RAB5 endosomes and vacuoles in a plant-specific manner.",
